  "text": "In each plot, changes of aboveground biomass and graminoid coverage induced by G. menyuanensis were the differences between a 100 9 100 cm quadrat without grassland caterpillars and a 40 9 40 cm cage with grassland caterpillars. A nondestructive sampling method was described in detail by [CITATION_1] to estimate aboveground biomass. The equation used to simulate aboveground biomass (AGB) was AGB = À5.7575 + 0.0839C + 5.6656H (r 2 = 0.84, n = 210, P < 0.001), where C is the total sward coverage and H is mean sward height. The mean height and mean coverage were measured using the 100 9 100 cm quadrat divided into 400 squares (5 9 5 cm) and the 40 9 40 cm cage divided into 100 squares (4 9 4 cm). Mean coverage of different species was calculated as the total coverage in squares with species presence divided by the total number squares. Graminoid coverage was calculated as the sum of mean coverage of each graminoid species.",
